<BODY>
<HEADLINE> St. Lucia Eliminated in Shootout  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   One day after Grenada became the first team
eliminated in World
Cup qualifying, another Caribbean island, St. Lucia, was the first
country knocked out by a penalty kick shootout.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Suriname won the shootout 3-1 after each country took 1-0
victories in the home-and-home first-round CONCACAF series.
</P>
<P>
   Suriname's Alberto Doesburj scored the only goal of the game in
the 80th minute. Because St. Lucia won the first game by the same
score on March 5, an overtime was played to decide the winner.
</P>
<P>
   After the overtime ended scoreless, Suriname's Benny Kiansi,
Orlando Grootfaam and Werner Blackson scored in a shootout against
goalie Abraham Mentor. Valencius Joseph was the only St. Lucian
kicker to get one past Surinamese goalie Roel Tempo.
</P>
<P>
   St. Vincent and the Grenadines completed a rout of the U.S.
Virgin Islands with a 5-1 victory Sunday. That followed an earlier
9-0 win.
</P>
<P>
   Despite missing five starters who were playing abroad, St.
Vincent and the Grenadines dominated. Striker James Chewitt had
four goals.
</P>
<P>
   St. Vincent will next play . Kitts on April 16.
</P>
<P>
   Also finishing off a one-sided series was Bermuda, which romped
past the British Virgin Islands 9-0 for a 14-1 aggregate.
</P>
<P>
   At Hamilton, the hosts scored seven second-half goals. Stephen
Astwood and substitute John Barry Nusum led with two goals apiece
to advance to a series with Antigua and Barbuda.
</P>
<P>
   The Bahamas advanced by beating Anguilla 2-1 for a 5-1 aggregate
total.
</P>
<P>
   On a soggy home field in Nassau, Bahamas striker Anton Haven
shot the ball over the head of goalie Ryan Liddie from 40 yards in
the 16th minute. Kevin Davies scored the deciding goal in the 77th
minute off a pass by Peron Major.
</P>
<P>
   Anguilla's only goal came in the 40th minute on a penalty kick
by midfielder Richard O'Conner. He got the score on his second try
after his first attempt was called back for jumping the referee's
whistle.
</P>
<P>
   The Bahamas faces Haiti next.
</P>
<P>
   Haiti defeated Dominica 3-1 for a 7-1 aggregate. Haitian striker
Golman Pierre scored a hat trick, getting all three in the second
half after Dominica took the lead.
</P>
<P>
   Cuba advanced 4-0 with a scoreless tie at the Cayman Islands.
</P>
<P>
   In a game moved to Port-of-Spain, Trinidad because of volanic
activity on Montserrat, the Dominican Republic beat Montserrat,
3-1. The Dominicans advanced with a 6-1 aggregate and will play
Trinidad and Tobago in the next round.
</P>
<P>
   In the Central America round-robin, Panama beat Nicaragua 2-0
and Guatemala defeated Belize 2-1.
</P>
<P>
   Visiting Panama pressed on offense throughout, getting an early
goal from Mario Mendez and a late one by Julio Cesar Dely Valdes.
</P>
<P>
   In a game moved to Honduras because of current political
conflicts between the two countries, Guatemala won it in the 76th
minute on Ruddy Ramirez's goal. Fredy Garcia also scored for
Guatemala, in the 33rd minute, while Emory Nunez got Belize's goal
in the 40th minute in stifling heat.
</P>
<P>
   Sunday's game took place in the northern city of San Pedro Sula
after FIFA ruled it be played in neutral territory because of the
''dangerous border situation between the two countries.''
</P>
<P>
   Tions have been involved in a border dispute for more than 100
years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
