<HEADLINE> Dow Rises 39; Nasdaq Gains 12  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 39 points
in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a 4-3 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 12 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is up two points.
</P>
<P>
   Traders anticipate the market will be more toned-down this week,
after several days of hyper-volatility last week.
</P>
<P>
   The primary reason for caution is tomorrow's meeting of the
Federal Reserve's policy panel.
</P>
<P>
   And even though a quarter-point hike in short-term rates is
considered close to a sure thing, the likelihood is that investors
will wait until after the Fed announces the hike before staking out
new positions.
</P>
<P>
   There will be some earnings news this week, with numbers later
today from 3-Com.
</P>
<P>
   Stocks in Europe have been higher, after Asian markets were
mostly lower.
</P>
