<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 11:10 a.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
Monday, March 20, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dow Up 74; Nasdaq Down 18
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mixed in early trading today as
investors waited to see whether the Federal Reserve will raise
interest rates at its meeting tomorrow. Many on Wall Street are
expecting the Fed to raise interest rates by a quarter-percentage
point, which would be the fifth increase since last June. Just
before 11 a.m., the Dow industrials were up 74.46 at 10,669. 69. On
the NYSE, advancers led decliners 1,309-1,172. The Nasdaq was down
18.58. Financial stocks were mostly higher after Lehman Brothers
reported first-quarter earnings well above Wall Street's
expectations. Lehman Brothers stock was up 13/16 at 92\. Several
other Wall Street firms that are scheduled to release their
earnings this week also rose.
</P>
<P>
   Financial Figures
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures as of 11 a.m. EST:
