<HEADLINE> VF Corp. Buys Sunbeam's Backpack  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Apparel maker VF Corp. is buying Sunbeam
Corp.'s Eastpak business, which includes backpacks, book bags and
other school accessories.
</P>
<P>
   Terms of the agreement, announced Monday, were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   The Eastpak products will be rolled into VF's existing JanSport
division, based in Appleton, Wis., VF officials said. JanSport is
the world's largest marketer of backpacks and a leading producer
and marketer of outdoor-oriented equipment, luggage, apparel,
accessories and travel packs.
</P>
<P>
   With $5.6 billion in annual sales, Greensboro-based VF is the
world's largest apparel company and a leader in jeanswear, intimate
apparel, workwear, knitwear, playwear, daypacks and swimwear. Its
principal brands include Lee, Wrangler, Riders, Rustler, Vanity
Fair, Vassarette, Bestform, Lily of France, Healthtex, Jantzen and
Red Kap.
</P>
<P>
   Sunbeam Corp., based on Boca Raton, Fla., designs, manufactures
and markets consumer products under brand names including Sunbeam,
Mr. Coffee and Oster.
</P>
