<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed, Gold Up in Europe  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was higher against the yen and
mixed against other major currencies in European trading today.
Gold rose.
</P>
<P>
   The euro was quoted at 97.14 cents in late European trading, up
from 97.12 cents on Friday. Later, in midday trading in New York,
the euro traded at 97.17 cents.
</P>
<P>
   Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Friday,
included 106.50 Japanese yen, up from 106.12; 1.6598 Swiss francs,
up from 1.6586; 1.4694 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4728.
</P>
<P>
   The British pound was quoted at $1.5685, down from $1.5718.
</P>
<P>
   In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 106.31 yen, and
the pound was worth $1.5696.
</P>
<P>
   Based on euro rates, the dollar is worth 2.0130 German marks,
down from 2.0132; 6.7506 French francs, down from 6.7520; 2.2644
Dutch guilders, down from 2.2674; 1,992.66 Italian lire, up from
1,992.25.
</P>
<P>
   Gold dealers in London fixed a recommended price of $284.50 bid
per troy ounce late afternoon, up from $283.80 on Friday. In Zurich
the bid price was $284.25, up from $283.20. Gold rose 5 cents in
Hong Kong to $285.05.
</P>
<P>
   Silver in London was unchanged at $5.04 bid per troy ounce.
</P>
