<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 3:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
Monday, March 20, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Stocks Mixed; Dow Up 19
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue-chip stocks rose today, but the broader
market held back as nervous investors waited to see whether the
Federal Reserve will raise interest rates at its meeting tomorrow.
Many on Wall Street are expecting the Fed to raise interest rates
by a quarter-percentage point, but John H. Shaughnessy, chief
investment strategist at Advest Inc., said that believes Fed
Chairman Alan Greenspan won't act aggressively for the remainder of
the year. Just before 3 p.m., the Dow was up 19.86 at 10,615.09. On
the NYSE, decliners edged advancers 1,487-1,423. The Nasdaq fell
169.26 to 4,628.87, fueled by a drop in MicroStrategy, a maker of
software used in electronic commerce. MicroStrategy lost more than
half its value, with shares plummeting 127 21/64 to 99 27/64 after
the company revised its financial results for 1998 and 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Financial Figures
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures as of 3 p.m. EST:
Dow Industrials:        10615.09  + 19.86
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1423  Declines 1487  Unchgd  489
