<HEADLINE> Summary of Supreme Court Action  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   The Supreme Court took these actions Monday:
<TEXT>
<P>
   --Let stand a ruling that bars race as a factor when public
school students seek to transfer to another school. The justices
refused to let a Maryland school district veto a white boy's
transfer to a mostly white magnet school from his
minority-dominated neighborhood school.
</P>
<P>
   --Rejected the free-speech appeal of an inmate who wanted to have
Playboy magazine delivered to his cell and left intact an Arizona
county's ban on all depictions of frontal nudity from its jails.
</P>
<P>
   --Agreed to consider squelching a convicted rapist's attempt to
get out from under his designation in Washington state as a
sexually violent predator who should stay locked up even after he
serves his prison sentence.
</P>
<P>
   --Turned down an appeal by a Louisiana man who won, then lost, a
$1 million award from jail officials who failed to protect him from
gouging out his own eyes during a psychotic episode.
</P>
<P>
   --Rejected an appeal in which a North Carolina newspaper, The
Charlotte Observer, urged the justices to rule that the public and
news media have a constitutional right to attend civil trials even
when some participants want to exclude them.
</P>
<P>
   --Voted to decide in a California case whether the government can
be forced to pay for property damage caused by water from federally
sponsored irrigation projects.
</P>
</TEXT>
