<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
Monday, March 20, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Nasdaq Drops 187,62; Dow Up 85.01
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Nasdaq composite index fell sharply today,
closing down 187.62 at 4,610.51. The Dow Jones industrial average
was up 85.01 at 10,680.24. The Dow and the Nasdaq diverged as
investors drew money out of lesser-known names in the software and
biotechnology groups and poured it into the largest, most dominant
technology companies. Hewlett-Packard, Intel and IBM led the Dow's
advance. Several factors combined to derail the Nasdaq.
MicroStrategy, a maker of software used in electronic commerce,
lost more than half its value after the company revised its
financial results for 1998 and 1999. MicroStrategy shares were down
140 at 86}. Internet retailers also were mostly lower after
Barron's magazine reported this weekend that dozens of prominent
companies are strapped for cash.
</P>
<P>
   Financial Figures
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures as of Monday's close:
Dow Industrials:        10,680.24  + 85.01
