<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Skier at Little Whiteface Mountain dies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WILMINGTON, N.Y. (AP) -- A 25-year-old Albany man died after
hitting a tree while skiing at Little Whiteface Mountain.
</P>
<P>
   Brendon Prostko, a graduate student at the State University of
New York's Albany campus, was skiing the intermediate-level
Excelsior Trail on Sunday when he went off the trail and into the
woods, said Sandy Caligiore, director of communications for the
Olympic Regional Development Authority. Little Whiteface is
adjacent to the larger Whiteface Mountain.
</P>
<P>
   Emergency personnel were contacted by another skier who called
on his cell phone at about 3:30 p.m. after discovering Prostko's
body about eight feet off the trail. How long Prostko had been
lying there was unknown. Prostko was taken to Adirondack Medical
Center in nearby Lake Placid, where he died from multiple traumatic
injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Caligiore said it appeared Prostko was skiing alone because
there were no witnesses to the accident and no one reported him
missing. The man's parents were notified in Virginia of their son's
death, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
