<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moved substantially or traded
heavily Monday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Walt Disney Co., up 2| to 39 7/16
</P>
<P>
   David Londoner, an analyst at Schroeder Securities, raised his
rating on Disney stock to ''outperform significantly'' from
''outperform.'' Londoner said he expects Disney shares to reach 47
within a year.
</P>
<P>
Eastman Chemical Co., up 3} to 43 9/16
</P>
<P>
   The company expects first-quarter earnings to beat even the most
optimistic projections of 65 cents a share. The First Call/Thomson
Financial consensus estimate is 43 cents a share for the quarter.
Eastman said its results reflect cost reductions and higher prices
for many of products.
</P>
<P>
American Italian Pasta Co., up 2 5/16 to 22[
</P>
<P>
   The company's board approved the repurchase of up to 1 million
shares for up to $25 million during the next 12 months. In its
announcement, American Italian Pasta said that while its stock
price has suffered, its business is strong and it expects to meet
earnings expectations. The company makes Mueller's pasta as well as
its own brands.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
MicroStrategy Inc., down 140 at 86}
</P>
<P>
   The electronic-commerce software company revised its financial
results for 1998 and 1999, deferring some of the revenue it had
recorded from large contracts in those years. The changes leave
MicroStrategy with a loss of between 43 cents and 51 cents per
share in 1999, compared with reported operating income of 15 cents
per share.
</P>
<P>
Saf T Lok Inc., up 7/32 at 3 9/16
</P>
<P>
   On Friday, handgun maker Smith &AMP; Wesson agreed to a wide range
of changes, including installing locks in its weapons and allowing
sales only by authorized dealers who obey tough restrictions. Saf T
Lok is expected to benefit.
</P>
<P>
Collateral Therapeutics Inc., up 14 7/16 at 40 3/16
</P>
<P>
   The company reported positive results from Phase I and Phase 2
tests of its angina drug, and plans to begin large-scale Phase 2b
and Phase 3 trials. Collateral's product is a non-surgical
cardiovascular gene therapy.
</P>
<P>
PurchasePro.com, down 22{ at 129\
</P>
<P>
   America Online Inc. and PurchasePro.com formed a three-year
alliance through which several AOL business users will adopt
electronic-commerce systems run by PurchasePro.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
