<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000320.0170 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-20 18:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Berlitz International CEO To Retire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Berlitz International Inc., the world's
largest language instruction company, on Monday announced the
retirement of its vice chairman, chief executive and president
Hiromasa Yokoi.
</P>
<P>
   The retirement is effective June 30, the company said.
</P>
<P>
   Yokoi is to remain on the board of directors for the next two
years. He joined the board in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   James Kahl will succeed Yokoi as vice chairman, effective July
1. Kahl previously served as chairman, chief executive and
president of La Petite Academy from 1993 until Dec. 31, 1999. He
will report to Berlitz Chairman Soichiro Fukutake.
</P>
<P>
   The company also announced it has created two subsidiaries to
begin operations on July 1. Berlitz Language Services will include
language instruction, publishing, franchising, cross-cultural
training and ELS Language Centers. Berlitz GlobalNET, an extension
of the company's translation business, will focus on
language-related document management, software, translation and
interpretation services.
</P>
<P>
   The 120-year-old company has more than 450 centers in more than
50 countries.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of Berlitz were unchanged at $15.81\ in trading on the
New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
</TEXT>
