<HEADLINE> 'Brockovich' Squashes Other Films  </HEADLINE>
By TOM HARRIGAN, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Julia Roberts swept into theaters as
tough-talking ''Erin Brockovich'' and captured a superstar share of
weekend film receipts: $28.1 million.
</P>
<P>
   The film's debut at No. 1 earned more than the next three films
combined. The previous weekend's leader ''Mission to Mars'' dropped
50 percent from its debut earnings to finish second at $11.4
million. ''Final Destination'' was No. 3 with $10 million in its
opening, according to final weekend figures released Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ''Erin Brockovich'' had the second-highest March opening ever --
just behind the $31.4 million of Jim Carrey's ''Liar, Liar'' in
1997. It was also the second-best Roberts' film debut behind last
July's $30 million for ''Runaway Bride,'' said Exhibitor Relations
Co. Inc., which charts the box office.
</P>
