<HEADLINE> Holloway Questionable For Friday  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SOUTH ORANGE, N.J. (AP) -- Seton Hall point guard Shaheen
Holloway needed crutches to walk on his sprained left ankle Monday.
His status is questionable for Friday's game against Oklahoma State
in the NCAA tournament.
</P>
<P>
   Holloway, who converted a full-court driving layup on Friday to
give Seton Hall a 72-71 overtime win over Oregon, had a second set
of X-rays taken of the ankle Monday. They were also negative, Seton
Hall sports information director Marie Wozniak said.
</P>
<P>
   An MRI was also performed to examine the ligament, but the
results won't be known until Tuesday, she said.
</P>
<P>
   The senior was treated with ice and electric stimulation on
Monday. Holloway also is wearing a compression boot.
</P>
<P>
   Holloway sustained a high sprain of the left ankle in the first
half of a 67-65 overtime win over Temple in the second round
Sunday. Ty Shine, his replacement, scored a career-high 26 points
and hit a game-winning 3-pointer with 18.9 seconds to play.
</P>
