<HEADLINE> Baseball, Umps Reach Tentative Deal  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Major League Baseball and the World Umpires
Association reached a tentative agreement Monday that will assure
an orderly start to the upcoming season.
</P>
<P>
   With negotiations still ongoing for a long-term basic agreement,
the sides agreed to have the commissioner's office assume
responsibility for all umpiring in the major leagues.
</P>
<P>
   The former American and National League umpiring staffs will be
combined into a new group that will handle games in both leagues.
</P>
<P>
   The WUA was granted certain retroactive commitments and other
terms.
</P>
