<HEADLINE> Orlando Coach Fined For Comments  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP)-- Orlando Magic coach Doc Rivers was fined $7,500
by the NBA on Monday for criticizing the officials after Friday's
Magic-Raptors game in Toronto.
</P>
<P>
   Rivers was upset that his team shot only 13 free throws -- the
same number that Vince Carter of Toronto attempted.
</P>
<P>
   The referees ''may as well as been wearing Raptors jerseys and
cheering for Vince Carter,'' Rivers said. ''The bottom line is we
have a bunch of guys with no names. John Amaechi gets bumped -- no
foul. Vince Carter gets bumped -- foul.''
</P>
<P>
   Asked what the NBA's reaction will be, Rivers said: ''They'll
fine me, but they'll agree with me.''
</P>
<P>
   The fine was issued by NBA vice president Rod Thorn.
</P>
<P>
   Before Monday night's game in Chicago, Rivers said: ''I did it,
I regret it.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't have a problem with the fine. I just thought my
players needed someone to stand up for them.''
</P>
</TEXT>
