<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Underworld Figure Slain in Belgrade  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) -- A prominent underworld figure and
former paramilitary leader was shot and killed in Belgrade on
Monday -- yet another in a series of recent gangland-style
assassinations.
</P>
<P>
   Branislav Lainovic was killed in front of the Hotel Serbia in a
Belgrade residential area, Beta news agency reported. The agency
quoted witnesses as saying they heard three shots around 4 p.m. and
then saw a young man running away.
</P>
<P>
   Lainovic was believed to control the crime network in the
northern city of Novi Sad, about 45 miles north of Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
   Lainovic was also a former commander of the Serb Guard, a
paramilitary group organized by opposition Serbian Renewal Movement
which fought on the side of the Serb rebels in Croatia at the start
of the war there in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   In January, Serbia's notorious warlord Zeljko Raznatovic, also
known as Arkan, was killed in a Belgrade hotel. Weeks later,
Yugoslav Defense Minister Pavle Bulatovic was gunned down in a
restaurant.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
